I see no reason to use objects in your case, but also don&#39;t think that using them would greatly impact performance. Personally, if I did not have a specific reason to use objects &amp;mdash; like for example the need for an `ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt;` or any other generic collection &amp;mdash; I would use primitives.

Then again, if I did need a huge collection of integers I would work with arrays (_e.g._ `int[]`).

**Edit:** Someone in the comments asked why people prefer `List&lt;T&gt;` as opposed to traditional arrays. Collections such as `ArrayList&lt;T&gt;` are mutable and easy to work with. Compare adding an element to an `ArrayList&lt;T&gt;`:

```java
List&lt;MyClass&gt; collection = new ArrayList&lt;MyClass&gt;();
collection.add(new MyClass());
